Description: 
  A script that makes a draggable, resizable window which displays a picture based on the room you're in. 
  It's meant to be used to make cooler looking maps, but I haven't made any maps yet, so it's just a concept for now!
  This is my first time messing around with making popup windows and the like so please message me if it's broken or something!
  Add room ID's and links to pictures in the code of the trigger for it to actually work!
  Note: closing the window won't disable the script, it'll pop back up when you leave the room. Use <picmaps off> to disable it.
Usage: picmaps on | off

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Optional alias : Makes it way easier to assign images to rooms

Usage:
  Roomhere ID(appends room ID plus an empty spot to put the link)
  Roomhere [link](gives you the current room ID plus whatever link you pasted, ready to drop into the trigger's code)

Alias: roomhere

Execute Javascript:

var roomid = gwc.gmcp.data.room.id
var textcolor = "#ffbe0d"
let input = args["*"];

function out(text, color) {
      gwc.output.append(text, color || textcolor)
  }

if (input && input.startsWith("http")){
  out('"' + roomid + '"' + " : " + '"' + input + '"')
}

else if (/^id$/i.test(input)) {
  out('"' + roomid + '"' + ":" + '"' + "link" + '"')
}

//Detect links

else{
  out("Usage: <roomhere imglink> or <roomhere ID>")
   }

